The front grille of the vehicle in the image is a prominent feature, occupying a significant portion of the front fascia. The grille's color appears to be a dark metallic gray or silver, which contrasts well with the gold-brown body of the SUV. The texture seems smooth and polished, reflecting light subtly, which adds to its premium look. The grille's pattern consists of horizontal bars that are evenly spaced, creating a clean and organized aesthetic.

At the center of the grille, there is a circular badge featuring a stylized "Buick" logo. This badge is a distinctive feature that immediately identifies the vehicle as a Buick model. The badge is smaller in size compared to the overall grille but is strategically placed to draw attention, serving as a focal point for brand recognition.

The tires are standard black rubber, typical for an SUV, and are mounted on the chrome wheels. The combination of the chrome finish and the multi-spoke design gives the wheels a luxurious and modern appearance, distinguishing them from simpler or more utilitarian wheel designs often seen on other vehicles in their category.
